        "title": "feat(provider): add DigitalOcean direct SSH provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add a DigitalOcean direct SSH lease provider with Droplet lifecycle, per-lease SSH keys, ownership tags, cleanup, touch, resolve, doctor, and Tailscale metadata support\n- add provider docs, config/env handling, smoke-script coverage, and guarded live DigitalOcean smoke support\n- harden DigitalOcean resource cleanup for failed acquire paths, tag replacement, stale SSH-key reuse, scoped env defaults, and DigitalOcean-valid tag encoding\n\n## Verification\n- `go test ./...`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `go build -trimpath -o bin/crabbox ./cmd/crabbox`\n- `node --test scripts/live-digitalocean-smoke.test.js`\n- `scripts/check-docs.sh`\n- `go test -race ./...`\n- `CRABBOX_LIVE=1 CRABBOX_LIVE_PROVIDERS=digitalocean scripts/live-digitalocean-smoke.sh`\n- `bin/crabbox list --provider digitalocean --json` after live smoke returned `[]`\n- `~/.codex/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` returned clean\n\n## Live Smoke\nLatest guarded DigitalOcean smoke completed with `classification=live_digitalocean_smoke_passed`, slug `digitalocean-smoke-20260610222841-76195`, and `cleanup=complete`. A post-smoke DigitalOcean provider inventory check returned `[]`.\n\nCloses #261\n",
